LLMs are statistical models, so what happens when you ask for something random? 

> give me a 10,000 character random string

The returned string was 63,984 characters long and cost me $1.15, not sure that was the best use of money, but it was
interesting. I think it would've been infinitely long because it only stopped due to an error "*The response is
incomplete because it exceeded the model's output limit.*"

What about the first part that we've ignored so far? Well, I think it gives the key for where the whole thing came from,
namely [this project on GitHub](https://github.com/stakpak/agent/blob/755a9c1f1f27a96c01f3d6380967a99c55d51c52/libs/shared/src/secrets/mod.rs\#L367)

It gives placeholder credentials all of which follow very similar patterns to the ones we've observed and includes the
first 6 characters `Kx9mP2` verbatim:

```
"myapp_api_key = \"abc123def456ghi789jklmnop\"",
"export SECRET_TOKEN=Kx9mP2nQ8rT4vW7yZ3cF6hJ1lN5sA0bD8eF",
"app.auth.password: 9k2L8pMvB3nQ7rX1ZdF5GhJwY4AsPo6C8mN",
"config.access_key=\"RaNd0mH1ghEnTr0pyV4luE567890abcdef\";",
"DB_CREDENTIALS=xy9mP2nQ8rT4vW7yZ3cF6hJ1lN5sAdefghij",
```
